{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Converts description definitions to a debugger Type Summary."}],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/debugdescription()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@attached"},{"kind":"text","text":"(member) "},{"kind":"attribute","text":"@attached"},{"kind":"text","text":"(memberAttribute) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"macro"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DebugDescription"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This macro converts compatible description implementations written in Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to an LLDB format known as a Type Summary. A Type Summary is LLDB’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"equivalent to "},{"code":"debugDescription","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", with the distinction that it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"execute code inside the debugged process. By avoiding code execution,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descriptions can be produced faster, without potential side effects, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shown in situations where code execution is not performed, such as the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"variable list of an IDE.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider this an example. This "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Team"},{"type":"text","text":" struct has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"summarizes some key details, such as the team’s name. The debugger only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"computes this string on demand - typically via the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"po"},{"type":"text","text":" command. By applying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, a matching Type Summary is constructed. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allows the user to show a string like “Rams [11-2]”, without executing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":". This improves the usability, performance, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reliability of the debugging experience."}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@DebugDescription","struct Team: CustomDebugStringConvertible {","   var name: String","   var wins, losses: Int","","   var debugDescription: String {","       \"\\(name) [\\(wins)-\\(losses)]\"","   }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"text":" macro supports both ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as well as a third option: a property named ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"text":". The first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"two are implemented when conforming to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomDebugStringConvertible"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomStringConvertible"},{"text":" protocols. The additional ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"property is useful when both ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"text":" are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implemented, but don’t meet the requirements of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macro. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"text":" is implemented, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"text":" choose it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"over ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"text":". Likewise, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"preferred over ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"Description Requirements","anchor":"Description-Requirements","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The description implementation has the following requirements:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The body of the description implementation must a single string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expression. String concatenation is not supported, use string interpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"String interpolation can reference stored properties only, functions calls","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and other arbitrary computation are not supported. Of note, conditional","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"logic and computed properties are not supported.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Overloaded string interpolation cannot be used."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/DebugDescription()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomReflectable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomLeafReflectable","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomPlaygroundDisplayConvertible","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/PlaygroundQuickLook"],"title":"Customizing Your Type’s Reflection","anchor":"Customizing-Your-Types-Reflection"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:s16DebugDescriptionyycfm","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"macro","roleHeading":"Macro","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"title":"DebugDescription()","fragments":[{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DebugDescription","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"/documentation/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/PlaygroundQuickLook":{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/PlaygroundQuickLook","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PlaygroundQuickLook","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PlaygroundQuickLook","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"/documentation/swift/playgroundquicklook","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The sum of types that can be used as a Quick Look representation."}],"title":"PlaygroundQuickLook","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/CustomReflectable":{"url":"/documentation/swift/customreflectable","role":"symbol","title":"CustomReflectable","fragments":[{"text":"protocol",